It's pretty and very addictive dungeon crawler. Not really rogue-like or, well, very casual one.

Pros:
- great game mechanic (it's simple and clear);
- 3 talent trees: mage, warrior and money-maker;
- game+ (game2+, game3+, ...) for infinite pleasure;
- back-story is good enough, beating the game is a pleasure.

Cons:
- low replayability (it rather makes more sense to continue playing with one char);
- tedious inventory micromanagement;
- primitive UI (missing keyboard shortcuts for many things, e.g. running from combat, all windows in one, not implemented big resolution support - things just get bigger, but not more);
- some features are unobvious to discover (some tips would be great), e.g. running from combat.

Definitely recommend to everyone.
